[{"id":"FT550293","type":"longtextV2","stimulusHtml":"Use the definition of the derivative to find<em> f</em>′(x) in terms of <em>f</em>(x) .","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"<p>Let <em> f </em> be a function that is everywhere differentiable and that has the following properties.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>(i) <span aria-label=\"f left parenthesis x plus h right parenthesis equals start fraction start numerator f of x plus f of h end numerator over start denominator f of negative x plus f of negative h end denominator end fraction\"><math> <mrow> <mi> f </mi> <mrow> <mo> ( </mo> <mrow> <mi> x </mi> <mo> + </mo> <mi> h </mi> </mrow> <mo> ) </mo> </mrow> <mo> = </mo> <mfrac> <mrow> <mi> f </mi> <mrow> <mo> ( </mo> <mi> x </mi> <mo> ) </mo> </mrow> <mo> + </mo> <mi> f </mi> <mrow> <mo> ( </mo> <mi> h </mi> <mo> ) </mo> </mrow> </mrow> <mrow> <mi> f </mi> <mrow> <mo> ( </mo> <mrow> <mo> − </mo> <mi> x </mi> </mrow> <mo> ) </mo> </mrow> <mo> + </mo> <mi> f </mi> <mrow> <mo> ( </mo> <mrow> <mo> − </mo> <mi> h </mi> </mrow> <mo> ) </mo> </mrow> </mrow> </mfrac> </mrow> </math></span> for all real numbers <em> h </em> and <em> x </em> (ii) <span aria-label=\"f of x greater than 0\"><math> <mrow> <mi> f </mi> <mrow> <mo> ( </mo> <mi> x </mi> <mo> ) </mo> </mrow> <mo> &gt; </mo> <mn> 0 </mn> </mrow> </math></span> for all real numbers <em> x </em> . (iii) <span aria-label=\"f prime of 0 equals negative 1\"><math> <mrow> <msup> <mi> f </mi> <mo> ′ </mo> </msup> <mrow> <mo> ( </mo> <mn> 0 </mn> <mo> ) </mo> </mrow> <mo> = </mo> <mo> − </mo> <mn> 1 </mn> </mrow> </math></span> .</p>\n"}]}]